Make sure each lecture includes the link to the MySQL documentation for that command

Connect to the MySQL server (may need -h option)
Create a MySQL Database
Create a User for the Database (differentiate between the database user and the user who signs in to the application)
Manage Privileges for the User for the Database
Manually Back Up the Database
Manually Restore the Database
Reset a User's password
Assign indexes to tables and other TABLE alters
Use the mysql -exec "tricks"

I've created an SQL script to populate a database with tables for them.
It's a stub of the mysql database.
They should first CREATE DATABASE testdb;
Then they should mysql -u theiruser testdb < testdb.sql
